WEBVTT

00:05.468 --> 00:07.902
<i>In New York
city's war on crime,</i>

00:07.903 --> 00:10.971
<i>the worst criminal offenders
are pursued</i>

00:10.972 --> 00:13.274
<i>by the detectives
of the Major Case Squad.</i>

00:13.275 --> 00:15.243
<i>These are their stories.</i>

00:21.870 --> 00:23.238
- So sorry, ladies.

00:23.239 --> 00:25.575
Sorry, ladies, I'm running late.
Catch me after the show.

00:25.576 --> 00:28.078
I'm all yours, I promise.
I'm late. I'm late.

00:30.214 --> 00:33.457
- You better hurry... Amanda
just gave the go-ahead to Brice.

00:33.458 --> 00:35.998
- Six months of previews
and not once with an understudy?

00:35.999 --> 00:37.203
I'm ten minutes late.

00:37.204 --> 00:38.989
- I know, but you know Amanda.
She panics.

00:40.459 --> 00:43.444
- Ethereal, spectacular.
Perfect!

00:43.445 --> 00:46.413
- Calm down, everybody.
I'm here. I'm here.

00:46.414 --> 00:48.048
- Well, so you are.

00:48.049 --> 00:50.050
- Sorry, buddy.
- No worries.

00:50.051 --> 00:53.924
- All right,
let's get Marc hooked up.

00:53.925 --> 00:55.959
- Sorry.
- All right...

00:55.960 --> 00:59.227
Now, remember, in the scene
where you defy daedalus,

00:59.228 --> 01:00.361
don't push.

01:00.362 --> 01:01.495
Just be.
- Yeah.

01:01.496 --> 01:04.797
I am.
I am icarus.

01:04.798 --> 01:07.166
- I'm talking
about hitting the note on-key,

01:07.167 --> 01:08.370
for once.
- I get it.

01:08.371 --> 01:10.706
Amanda, trust me.
- All right?

01:10.707 --> 01:13.176
- I got you the Cobb.
You haven't eaten all day.

01:13.177 --> 01:16.480
- I don't need a salad.
I need a drink.

01:16.481 --> 01:19.352
And get me Evan korman
on the phone!

01:19.353 --> 01:20.486
- Hello, Amanda.

01:20.487 --> 01:22.656
- Marc has to go.

01:22.657 --> 01:24.058
He's getting laughs in places

01:24.059 --> 01:25.727
where the audience
should be crying.

01:25.728 --> 01:30.066
It wasn't my idea to hire
a sitcom star.

01:30.067 --> 01:32.535
You said you needed a name.
- Yeah. You know why...

01:32.536 --> 01:36.105
because you ripped out 200 seats
to build your labyrinth.

01:36.106 --> 01:38.859
We lose 20 grand in ticket sales
every night.

01:40.795 --> 01:42.579
- Adam!
Jeez, you shouldn't have.

01:42.580 --> 01:44.180
I...
- Well, I didn't.

01:44.181 --> 01:46.583
They were outside your door.

01:46.584 --> 01:48.084
- Did you, uh, hear rehearsal?

01:48.085 --> 01:50.054
I think I nailed
that b-flat in <i>Labyrinth.</i>

01:50.055 --> 01:52.090
- Did you tell Amanda

01:52.091 --> 01:54.392
that you have a problem
with the minotaur number?

01:54.393 --> 01:58.430
- No.
I would never do that.

01:58.431 --> 02:00.766
- Well, she sends me an email

02:00.767 --> 02:04.037
saying the song
isn't <i>big</i> enough.

02:04.038 --> 02:06.874
- That's crazy.
You play 60,000-seat arenas.

02:06.875 --> 02:08.741
The song is brilliant.

02:08.743 --> 02:10.310
<i>- I'm getting</i>

02:10.311 --> 02:12.145
<i>high and higher</i>

02:12.146 --> 02:14.614
<i>I'm gonna touch the fire</i>

02:14.615 --> 02:15.715
- Stop!

02:17.051 --> 02:19.485
<i>- I'm gonna hold it in my hands</i>

02:19.486 --> 02:22.088
- The melody is still wrong.

02:22.089 --> 02:25.058
The audience needs to feel
dark, conflicted.

02:25.059 --> 02:26.994
- It's a Broadway musical,
Amanda.

02:26.995 --> 02:29.163
People want to feel happy.
- No, no, no, no.

02:29.164 --> 02:32.433
- The... the strings are...
they're too...

02:32.434 --> 02:34.302
They're too soaring.

02:34.303 --> 02:37.056
- He's flying, for God's sake.

02:42.413 --> 02:45.900
<i>I can't get any closer</i>

02:49.271 --> 02:52.491
<i>I'm falling back to earth</i>

02:52.492 --> 02:55.144
- What's happening?
- I don't know.

02:58.615 --> 03:00.049
- Aah!

03:01.319 --> 03:04.772
- Oh, my God.
Marc.

03:04.773 --> 03:06.357
- Bring in the curtain!

